# Entity tabs (`EntityTabsComponent`)

Shared tab bar for user portal **marketplace home** — **Tržište** / **Marketplace** (`/home`) — and **my listings** — **Moje objave** / **My listings** (`/our-listings`) hub pages. Also used on admin home hub (`/admin/home`).

## Component

| Path | Selector | Role |
|------|----------|------|
| `shared/ui/entity-tabs/` | `app-entity-tabs` | Pill tabs with Lucide icon + label |

### API

| Input / output | Type |
|----------------|------|
| `activeTab` | `UserEntityTab` or `AdminEntityTab` |
| `tabs` | `EntityTabConfig[]` — `{ id, labelKey, icon }` |
| `accentMode` | `'entity'` (default) \| `'neutral'` — user + admin hubs: entity accent on active pill; `'neutral'` only when tabs must stay uncolored |
| `tabChange` | output tab id |

Tab config:
- User: `portal/user/user-entity-tabs.config.ts` → `USER_ENTITY_TAB_CONFIG` (icons from `UserPageIcons`)
- Admin: `portal/admin/admin-entity-tabs.config.ts` → `ADMIN_ENTITY_TAB_CONFIG` (icons from `AdminPageIcons`)

**Active tab styling:** when `accentMode="entity"` (default on user + admin hubs), active pill gets `entity-context--{tab}` — entity border, soft fill, tinted icon. Inactive tabs stay neutral. See `entity-service-colors.mdc`.

### Tab sync (`syncHubEntityTab`)

Hub pages subscribe to `?tab=` via `syncHubEntityTab()` from `shared/utils/hub-tab-sync.ts`:

```typescript
syncHubEntityTab(this.route, this.destroyRef, parseUserEntityTab, this.activeTab);
```

Admin home uses `parseAdminEntityTab`. On tab change, navigate with `userMarketplaceUrl()` / `userOurListingsUrl()` / `adminHomeUrl()`.

### i18n

`portal.user.features.entityTabs.transport|freight|warehouse` + `…entityTabs.ariaLabel`

## URL convention

| Constant | Path / role |
|----------|-------------|
| `USER_HOME_URL` | `/home` — marketplace hub |
| `USER_OUR_LISTINGS_URL` | `/our-listings` — my listings hub |
| `userMarketplaceUrl(tab?)` | `/home?tab=transport` — marketplace tab navigation (`navigateByUrl()` only) |
| `userOurListingsUrl(tab?)` | `/our-listings?tab=transport` — my listings tab navigation |
| `userMarketplaceRoute(tab?)` | `{ route, queryParams }` — `[routerLink]` + `[queryParams]` for marketplace |
| `userOurListingsRoute(tab?)` | `{ route, queryParams }` — `[routerLink]` + `[queryParams]` for my listings |

Parse query with `parseUserEntityTab()` from `shared/constants/user-urls.ts`.

For `[routerLink]` in templates, use `userMarketplaceRoute()` / `userOurListingsRoute()`. Do **not** bind marketplace URL strings to `routerLink` (Angular encodes `?` into the path segment).

## Hub pages

| Feature | Route | Title keys | Icon | Table body |
|---------|-------|------------|------|------------|
| `features/home/` | `/home` | `pages.home.*` | `UserPageIcons.marketplace` (`LucideLayoutGrid`) | Embedded `*AllTablePageComponent` |
| `features/our-listings/` | `/our-listings` | `pages.ourListings.*` | `UserPageIcons.ourListings` (`LucideListChecks`) | Embedded `*OurTablePageComponent` |

User hubs: `PageHeaderComponent` + tab-specific `PrimaryActionLink` (publish CTA via `userCreateListingLabelKey()`). Admin home hub: same pattern with `adminCreateLabelKey()` from `admin-create-options.config.ts`.

### Hub copy (parallel structure)

| Hub | EN title | BS title | Subtitle pattern |
|-----|----------|----------|------------------|
| Marketplace | Marketplace | Tržište | Browse **other companies'** listings |
| My listings | My listings | Moje objave | Manage **your company's** listings |

Keys: `portal.user.pages.home.*`, `portal.user.pages.ourListings.*`.

List tables stay in feature `table-all/` / `table-our/` folders — **not** standalone routes.

### `.page-hub-header` wrapper (required)

Wrap **page header** (`PageHeader` + title + tab-specific publish CTA) and **`app-entity-tabs`** in `<div class="page-hub-header">`. Styles: `src/styles/_page-hub-header.scss` — `@use 'styles/page-hub-header';` in hub page SCSS.

```html
<div class="page-hub-header" [attr.data-entity-tab]="activeTab()">
  <app-page-header>
    <app-page-title titleKey="portal.user.pages.home.title" … [icon]="pageIcon" />
    <app-primary-action-link [route]="createUrl()" [labelKey]="createLabelKey()" />
  </app-page-header>
  <app-entity-tabs … />
  <a class="page-hub-header__cross-link" [routerLink]="crossLinkRoute().route" [queryParams]="crossLinkRoute().queryParams">
    {{ 'portal.user.pages.home.crossLink' | translate }}
  </a>
</div>
```

My listings hub: same pattern with `pages.ourListings.*` keys and `pages.ourListings.crossLink`.

Embedded table pages render **below** the wrapper. See `page-title.mdc`.

## Embedded table pages

Marketplace and our table page components render `DataTableComponent` only — no standalone page title/header. Hub pages own all chrome.

Our-listings tables may pass `emptyActionRoute` + `emptyActionLabelKey` to `DataTableComponent` for publish CTA on empty state.

## Admin hub

| Feature | Route | Tabs | Notes |
|---------|-------|------|-------|
| `portal/admin/features/home/` | `/admin/home?tab=` | users \| vehicles \| warehouses | `PageHeaderComponent` + tab-specific create CTA + `EntityTabsComponent` (default `accentMode="entity"`) |

Admin URL builder: `adminHomeUrl(tab?)`. Row click → `admin*DetailUrl(id)`; detail footer Edit/Delete.

**Hub header:** same `.page-hub-header` + `PageHeaderComponent` pattern as user hubs — tab-specific `PrimaryActionLink` via `createUrl()` / `adminCreateLabelKey(activeTab)`; labels `portal.admin.nav.createUser|createVehicle|createWarehouse`; routes `ADMIN_CREATE_*_URL`. Create also via topbar `EntityCreateMenuComponent` (`shared.topbar.create.openMenu`) with per-option entity colors from `ADMIN_CREATE_OPTIONS`.

Reference: `portal/admin/features/home/admin-home-page.component.*`. See `page-title.mdc`.

## Topbar navigation

- Brand → `USER_HOME_URL` (marketplace)
- Create → `EntityCreateMenuComponent` (`+` beside brand; `shared.topbar.offer.openMenu`)
- My listings → account menu only (`shared.topbar.account.profile` → `userOurListingsUrl()`; icon `LucideListChecks` in topbar)
- `user-topbar-nav.config.ts` — empty (`topbarNav: []`)

## Do not

- Register standalone `/transport`, `/freight`, `/warehouse`, or `*/our` list routes alongside hubs.
- Register a separate `/find` or `/offer` route — create flows use topbar `EntityCreateMenuComponent`.
- Hardcode `/home?tab=` strings — use URL builders from `user-urls.ts`.
- Render `app-entity-tabs` outside `.page-hub-header` on hub pages.
